    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Roman pottery characterized by its red color, smooth finish, and sometimes having decorations of stamped figures or patterns. It was found in Italy, Gaul, and Germany, and throughout the Roman Empire 1st century BCE-3rd century CE. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
